ensitive areas and information systems. The IAM system utilizes two-factor authentication (2FA) and dynamic password technology, generating over 5,000 unique access codes per day to minimize the risk of unauthorized access.\n- Investment in AI-driven security analytics tools capable of processing and analyzing over 100,000 security events per hour, enabling proactive identification of anomalous behavior patterns that could indicate cybersecurity threats.\n- Establishment of a 24/7 cybersecurity operations center (CSOC) staffed by a team of 50 cybersecurity professionals. The CSOC is equipped with state-of-the-art monitoring and response tools to ensure immediate action can be taken against identified threats.\n\nThese cybersecurity measures represent an investment exceeding $15 million, underscoring our commitment to maintaining the highest levels of security and privacy for our operations and passengers alike. The strategies outlined in the appendices are part of an ongoing effort to adapt to the evolving landscape of digital threats and safeguard Heathrow Terminal 5 as a global leader in airport security and efficiency."
